g.aria-label: Reduces the number of points used to generate your glyph, this can improve your handwriting's appearance
Sets the baseline of your glyph. A lower case letter "a" would be set at the bottom but the lower case letter "g" would need to be be set above the bottom of the glyph.
Increases the curvature used in your glyph, this can improve your handwriting's appearance
Sets the left edge of yuor glyph, you can use this to increase spacing or to overlap letters
Sets the right edge of yuor glyph, you can use this to increase spacing or to overlap letters

Indicates the current letter (glyph) to be written. The first one indicated by "_!" is the missing glyph character, it also sets the width of the space character. After each character is drawn click this to save and move on to the next glyph.
Clears the current glyph. Allows the user to redo the character
Displays a preview of the glyphs so far. Clicking this enables the Save icon which enables the TTF menu.
When enabled, this will open a menu to save the characters as a TTF file. Requires the svg2ttf node package. Once the file is generated use the svg file created in the data folder.
